<p>If $A$ is symmetric and invertible, then $A^{-1}$ is:</p>
</li>
<li>a) Skew-symmetric</li>
<li>b) Symmetric</li>
<li>c) The identity</li>
<li>d) The transpose of $A$<blockquote>
<p><strong>Correct answer: b)</strong> If $A^T=A$ and $A$ is invertible, then $(A^{-1})^T = (A^T)^{-1} = A^{-1}$, so $A^{-1}$ is also symmetric.</p>
</blockquote>
</li>
</ol>
