<p>A $2\times2$ system modelling a problem has infinitely many solutions. In the context of the problem, this means:</p>
</li>
<li>a) The problem has no solution</li>
<li>b) The problem data are inconsistent</li>
<li>c) The problem is underdetermined (there are insufficient conditions)</li>
<li>d) There is always an error in the formulation<blockquote>
