<h5>4.1.2 Basic operations: addition, subtraction, scalar multiplication and their properties</h5>

<p><strong>Worked Example</strong></p>
<p>Given $\mathbf{u} = (2, -1, 3)$ and $\mathbf{v} = (-1, 4, 2)$, compute:
(a) $\mathbf{u} + \mathbf{v}$, (b) $\mathbf{u} - \mathbf{v}$, (c) $3\mathbf{u} - 2\mathbf{v}$, (d) $|3\mathbf{u} - 2\mathbf{v}|$.</p>
<p><strong>Step-by-step Solution:</strong></p>
<p><strong>(a)</strong> $\mathbf{u} + \mathbf{v} = (2+(-1), -1+4, 3+2) = (1, 3, 5)$</p>
<p><strong>(b)</strong> $\mathbf{u} - \mathbf{v} = (2-(-1), -1-4, 3-2) = (3, -5, 1)$</p>
<p><strong>(c)</strong> $3\mathbf{u} = (6, -3, 9)$; $2\mathbf{v} = (-2, 8, 4)$;
$3\mathbf{u} - 2\mathbf{v} = (6-(-2), -3-8, 9-4) = (8, -11, 5)$</p>
<p><strong>(d)</strong> $|3\mathbf{u} - 2\mathbf{v}| = \sqrt{64 + 121 + 25} = \sqrt{210}$</p>
