<strong>(a)</strong> $\overrightarrow{AB}=(3,-2,-2)$, $\overrightarrow{BC}=(-2,3,-2)$, $\overrightarrow{CA}=(-1,-1,4)$.<br />
<strong>(b)</strong> $\overrightarrow{AB}+\overrightarrow{BC}+\overrightarrow{CA}=(3-2-1,-2+3-1,-2-2+4)=(0,0,0)$ ✓.<br />
<strong>(c)</strong> $|AB|=\sqrt{9+4+4}=\sqrt{17}$. $|BC|=\sqrt{4+9+4}=\sqrt{17}$. $|CA|=\sqrt{1+1+16}=\sqrt{18}=3\sqrt{2}$.<br />
Perimeter $= 2\sqrt{17}+3\sqrt{2}$.</p>
</blockquote>
